<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1893-11-25T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1893-11-25T00:00:00-05:00" n="665" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d665">
                    <head><hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Terrell</persName> to Mr.
                                <persName type="to">Gresham</persName>.</hi></head>
                    <opener><seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg></opener>
                    <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Legation of
                                    the United States</hi>,<lb/><hi rend="italic">Constantinople</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1893-11-25"><hi rend="italic">November 25, 1893</hi></date>.
                            (Received November 25.)</dateline></opener>
                    <p>Mr. Terrell reports the disapproval by the Sultan of the verbal agreement
                        made with the Sublime Porte that a refusal on the part of a naturalized
                        citizen of the United States born in Turkey to leave would be the only
                        ground on which such citizen could be imprisoned.</p>
                </div>
                </body></text></TEI>